BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:Cp-I1HGjb3mULDEg67xGS
SUMMARY:Red May 2026: ICE-Age Policing
DTSTAMP:20260411T040854Z
DTSTART:20260505T193000Z
DESCRIPTION:Red May\\\, a month-long spree of red arts\\\, red theory\\\, a
	nd red politics based in Seattle\\\, Washington\\\, gathers each spring to
	 discuss a world beyond capitalism. For this year’s event at Town Hall Sea
	ttle\\\, Red May brings together a panel to discuss policing in the age of
	 ICE. \\n“Counterinsurgency has come home. Since the end of the Vietnam Wa
	r\\\, innovations in militarized policing have come one after another. No 
	knock raids. AI surveillance. Clear and hold neighborhoods. Each new tacti
	c or strategy has been rubber-stamped in Congress by both Democrats and Re
	publicans under the guise of a never-ending War on Crime. Now\\\, the Trum
	p administration has fashioned its own masked Gestapo\; it has taken an ex
	isting organization designed for border control (ICE) and built it into a 
	private army serving at the prerogative of the President\\\, most egregiou
	sly for assaults on Democrat-run cities like Portland\\\, and Chicago and 
	the murder of protestors\\\, reclassified as ‘domestic terrorists.’ How di
	d we get here? How do we get out of here?” \\nJoin Red May and a panel of 
	scholars to guide us through the labyrinth.\n\nhttps://townhallseattle.org
	/event/red-may-2026/\n\nFrom Town Hall Seattle
URL:https://townhallseattle.org/event/red-may-2026/
LOCATION:The Wyncote NW Forum\\\, 1119 8th Ave (Entrance off Seneca St.)\\\
	, Seattle\\\, 98101\\\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:town-hall-seattle
CATEGORIES:Town Hall Seattle
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT
END:VEVENT
